## Overview

Once the ability to create a [streaming event header](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/361216) is released, we need to allow a group owner to see those headers via the GraphQL API.

## Proposal

Implement a query like this:

```graphql
query {
  group(fullPath: "example-group") {
    id
    externalAuditEventDestinations {
      nodes {
        destinationUrl
        verificationToken
        id
        headers { 
          nodes {
            key
            value
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Overview

Once it is possible to [create a streaming audit event HTTP header](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/361216), it should be possible to delete the same header via the GraphQL API.

## Proposal

* Create a GraphQL mutation to delete a streaming audit event HTTP header.

```graphql
mutation {
  externalAuditEventDestinationHeaderDestroy(input: { headerID: "gid://id/to/header" } ) {
    errors
  }
}
```

